# Initial Assumptions & Threat Considerations

## Risk Areas

### 1. Default Admin Account Usage

- High risk of credential compromise
- Lack of accountability

### 2. PAW Enforcement

- Any admin activity outside PAW = suspicious

### 3. Linux Systems

- Low activity baseline → anomalies are highly suspicious

### 4. Service Accounts

- Should:
    - Not login interactively
    - Not perform unexpected actions

## Detection Ideas

- Admin login outside PAW
- Service account interactive login
- Sudden Linux activity spike
- Use of sudo outside normal patterns
